-- Santander Said to Sell $3.4 Billion of Mortgage-Backed Bonds
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-01-18T15:25:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/santander-said-to-sell-3-4-billion-of-mortgage-backed-bonds.html
Santander U.K. Plc plans to sell
$3.4 billion of mortgage-backed securities in dollars, euros,
pounds and yen, according to three people with knowledge of the
transaction.  The sale includes $500 million of Class A1 notes with a
one-year average life that pay 20 basis points more than one-
month Libor, and $500 million of A2 dollar notes with a 2.8-year
life paying 165 basis points over three-month Libor, the people
said.  The sale also comprises 1.2 billion euros of A3 notes with
a 2.8-year life paying 155 basis points over benchmark rates,
175 million pounds of A4 notes due in 2.8 years with a 175
basis-point spread and 215 million pounds of A6 notes with a
4.9-year life paying 185 basis points, the people said.  The deal includes 20 billion yen of A5 notes due in 2.8
years paying a spread of 125 basis points.   The notes will be sold through Holmes Master Issuer Plc
Series 2012-1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
